SIMPLE: marshaling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marshaling
<hw>Mar"shal*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>marshalling</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of arranging in due order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>The arrangement of an escutcheon
to exhibit the alliances of the owner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Marshaling of assets</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>the
arranging or ranking of assets in due order of
administration.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marshalsea</ent>⟦br⟧
